The paper discusses the interaction mechanisms and influence dynamics among students in MOOCs, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the formulation of a learning network diffusion model, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the model and suggests ways to extend it, which involves computational modeling and simulation (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of MOOC forums, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the research on MOOC design and instruction, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
